CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 13, 1957, pg. 2 reads: " Police Integration - Another step in the gradual integration program of the City of Pittsburgh was the recent appointment of Desk Sgt. Edward Bailey, right, who is shown at work at East Liberty Police Station. On his right is Turnkey Joseph Boyle. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three men, including Joseph Boyle, center, and Desk Sgt. Edward Bailey, right, posed behind large desk in East Liberty Police Station
